race.description: Glen Innes Services Club Glen Innes Cup Handicap
race.comment: Competitive renewal of the Glen Innes Cup. UNLEASH (9) brings the right form to the race. Closed strongly to get up for second last start in open company over this distance at Chinchilla. Four-time winner at the trip who gets the perfect run out of gate two. Looks the one to beat with just 55kgs. GIDDAY GIDDAY (8) had been racing in great heart then endured a horrific five-wide run at Toowoomba last time and understandably dropped out. Kelsey Lenton has four wins and four placings on the mare from ten rides and is back on today. Can turn things around. ACCRUE (10) made a welcomed return to form last start when beaten under a length over 1450m at Quirindi. Up in class but drops a massive 9kgs which brings him into discussions. HE'S A COPY BOY (11) did a good job to finish a close fourth at Inverell recently when coming off a 32-day let-up. Back in trip which suits. Right in the mix. CAPO STRADA (1) will race handy and give backers a sight.
